icky with static initializers and property settings. If there’s a loading failure with Class.forName, we may need to adjust our approach.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing to invoke methods**\\n\\nI need to invoke the public static method for closeDirectByteBuffer. If the parameter LogNode is loaded in isolation, I'll use getMethod with the isolated logNodeClass to ensure it works. I’ll need to check that the result is true, since the helper clean method returns null.\\n\\nI also need to close the class loader and restore the java.version property afterward. Since there may be many tests running, especially with JUnit's order, it's essential to manage thread safety here, but it seems like there won't be issues with other threads.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering classgraph location**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to locate the classgraph jar using the protection domain method with FileUtils. By referencing the protection domain, I could find the current location of the code source. My concern is about loading FileUtils or VersionFinder too early in the process. If I import FileUtils for the first test, it looks like it might create some complications. I need to be careful to avoid premature loading.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying method accessibility**\\n\\nI'm exploring whether a public method in a private nested class can be accessed. I think calling `setAccessible(true)` on our own class might be allowed. But it seems that `Method.getMethod` only returns public methods if the class itself is public. If the nested class is private, will it still return its public members? To avoid these access issues, I should define a public static final class named `LegacyCleanerHooks` with public methods. That way, it will be accessible within a public test.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_GlEdE8715c5ZqM1OdmUtjXwH|fc_04a6c80d168625e7016a02807edce0819485ba5d53d2d8691b", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.github.classgraph/classgraph/4.8.108/src/test/java/io_github_classgraph/classgraph/FileUtilsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_github_classgraph.classgraph;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.regex.Pattern;\n\nimport nonapi.io.github.classgraph.utils.FileUtils;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class FileUtilsTest {\n    private static final String FILE_UTILS_CLASS_NAME = \"nonapi.io.github.classgraph.utils.FileUtils\";\n    private static final String LOG_NODE_CLASS_NAME = \"nonapi.io.github.classgraph.utils.LogNode\";\n    private static final String LEGACY_JAVA_VERSION = \"1.8.0_292\";\n\n    @Test\n    void closesDirectBufferWithCurrentRuntimeCleaner() {\n        final ByteBuffer byteBuffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(16);\n\n        assertThat(FileUtils.closeDirectByteBuffer(byteBuffer, null)).isTrue();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void invokesLegacyDirectBufferCleanerPathInIsolatedRuntimeView() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            invokeLegacyDirectBufferCleanerPath();\n        } catch (final InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            final Throwable cause = exception.getCause();\n            if (cause instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return;\n            }\n            throw exception;\n        } catch (final Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void invokeLegacyDirectBufferCleanerPath() throws Exception {\n        LegacyCleanerHooks.reset();\n        final String previousJavaVersion = System.getProperty(\"java.version\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.version\", LEGACY_JAVA_VERSION);\n        try (URLClassLoader isolatedClassLoader = new URLClassLoader(isolatedClassPath(), null)) {\n            final Class<?> fileUtilsClass = Class.forName(FILE_UTILS_CLASS_NAME, true, isolatedClassLoader);\n            installLegacyCleanerHooks(fileUtilsClass);\n\n            final Class<?> logNodeClass = Class.forName(LOG_NODE_CLASS_NAME, false, isolatedClassLoader);\n            final Method closeDirectByteBuffer = fileUtilsClass.getMethod(\"closeDirectByteBuffer\",\n                    ByteBuffer.class, logNodeClass);\n            final Object closed = closeDirectByteBuffer.invoke(null, ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(16), null);\n\n            assertThat(closed).isEqualTo(Boolean.TRUE);\n            assertThat(LegacyCleanerHooks.attachmentInvoked).isTrue();\n            assertThat(LegacyCleanerHooks.cleanerInvoked).isTrue();\n            assertThat(LegacyCleanerHooks.cleanInvoked).isTrue();\n        } finally {\n            restoreJavaVersion(previousJavaVersion);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void installLegacyCleanerHooks(final Class<?> fileUtilsClass) throws Exception {\n        setStaticField(fileUtilsClass, \"attachmentMethod\", LegacyCleanerHooks.class.getMethod(\"attachment\"));\n        setStaticField(fileUtilsClass, \"directByteBufferCleanerMethod\", LegacyCleanerHooks.class.getMethod(\"cleaner\"));\n        setStaticField(fileUtilsClass, \"cleanerCleanMethod\", LegacyCleanerHooks.class.getMethod(\"clean\"));\n    }\n\n    private static void setStaticField(final Class<?> targetClass, final String fieldName, final Object value)\n            throws Exception {\n        final Field field = targetClass.getDeclaredField(fieldName);\n        field.setAccessible(true);\n        field.set(null, value);\n    }\n\n    private static URL[] isolatedClassPath() throws Exception {\n        final CodeSource codeSource = FileUtils.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource();\n        if (codeSource != null && codeSource.getLocation() != null) {\n            return new URL[] { codeSource.getLocation() };\n        }\n        return Arrays.stream(System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\", \"\").split(Pattern.quote(File.pathSeparator)))\n                .filter(entry -> !entry.isEmpty())\n                .map(File::new)\n                .map(file -> {\n                    try {\n                        return file.toURI().toURL();\n                    } catch (final Exception exception) {\n                        throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Could not convert classpath entry to URL: \" + file,\n                                exception);\n                    }\n                })\n                .toArray(URL[]::new);\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreJavaVersion(final String previousJavaVersion) {\n        if (previousJavaVersion == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(\"java.version\");\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(\"java.version\", previousJavaVersion);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class LegacyCleanerHooks {\n        private static boolean attachmentInvoked;\n        private static boolean cleanerInvoked;\n        private static boolean cleanInvoked;\n\n        private LegacyCleanerHooks() {\n        }\n\n        public static Object attachment() {\n            attachmentInvoked = true;\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        public static Object cleaner() {\n            cleanerInvoked = true;\n            return new Object();\n        }\n\n        public static void clean() {\n            cleanInvoked = true;\n        }\n\n        private static void reset() {\n            attachmentInvoked = false;\n            cleanerInvoked = false;\n            cleanInvoked = false;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2682, "output": 3399, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29121, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778548833676, "responseId": "resp_04a6c80d168625e7016a0280623bf48194b1698725cfa53efd"}}
